The paper deals with online learning algorithms for A/B testing, which involves monitoring the performance of a feature as it is rolled out to different groups of users. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as the algorithms are designed to learn from data and make decisions based on that learning. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of these algorithms, which involves data structures and algorithms for efficient monitoring and analysis, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of monitoring user experience and performance, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
